    <title>ACM bundles on cubic threefolds and fourfolds containing a plane</title>
    <summary>  We study ACM bundles on cubic threefolds and fourfolds containing a plane.
For this purpose, we propose a new approach based on derived category
techniques. In the case of cubic threefolds, these techniques allow us to show
that the moduli space of Ulrich bundles is always non-empty. Applied to cubic
fourfolds containing a plane, they give us a way to recover the K3 surface
naturally associated to the fourfold as a moduli space of stable ACM bundles of
rank four.
</summary>
